node.text:
Back in 1986, Andy Warhol confessed he had “Bunnies on the Brain.” In honor of the legendary artist's birthday, here is a collection of his many contributions to Playboy that spanned over two decades. Read more at the link in bio

1. Polaroid collage of actress Patti D'Arbanville, from 1974 but published for the first time in 2017
2. Polaroid collage of actress Dominique Darel, from 1974 but published for the first time in 2017
3. Self-portrait of Warhol with his Polaroid published in a 1974 pictorial
4. Photocopied self-portraits published in a 1969 PLAYBOY profile
5. Silkscreen artwork published in a 1967 feature
6. January 1986 Cover artwork
